WEBVTT

00:02:55.920 --> 00:03:00.216
she was the kind of teacher
that was always in your business.

00:03:00.240 --> 00:03:01.976
(Laughter)

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:04.456
She was the kind of teacher that was like,

00:03:04.480 --> 00:03:07.616
"Victor, I'm here for you
whenever you're ready."

00:03:07.640 --> 00:03:08.840
(Laughter)

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:11.536
I wasn't ready.

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:15.200
But she understood one basic principle
about young people like me.

00:03:15.840 --> 00:03:17.120
We're like oysters.

00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:20.496
We're only going to open up
when we're ready,

00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:23.000
and if you're not there when we're ready,

00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:25.294
we're going to clam back up.

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:28.096
Ms. Russ was there for me.

00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:30.136
She was culturally relevant,